Package au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries

Class CoreQueries

  • java.lang.Object
    • au.edu.anu.rscs.aot.queries.CoreQueries
  • public class CoreQueries
extends java.lang.Object

    This class is a convenience class of static methods that brings together queries of all types.

    It is specially designed to work in interaction with the SequenceQuery.get(...) method to query particular elements of a Graph. Examples:

    return all the OUT edges of a node labelled 'blue':

     get(node,
        edges(Direction.OUT), 
        edgeListEndNodes(),
        selectZeroOrMany(hasTheLabel("blue")));

    return all the children of a (tree)node that have property color='red'

     get(node,
        children(), 
        selectZeroOrMany(hasProperty("color","blue")));
    Author:
    Shayne Flint - 26/3/2012
    refactored by Ian Davies - feb. 2021
